Text Mining Terms with Ngrams

Gorbunov Valerii

10 02 2020

Task: “Cколько раз за 2019 год в новостных лентах трёх сайтов встречается слово Стратегия или комбинация”государственная национальная политика“,”национальная политика“?”

Solution: сформировать датасет c N-граммами (из 1, 2, 3 слов, приведенных к начальной форме с помощью Yandex MyStem), отфильтровать по заданному списку терминов (словосочетаний).

knitr::opts_chunk$set(message = FALSE, warning = FALSE)
library(DT)
library(stringr)
library(tidyverse)
library(tidytext)
library(tidyr)
library(lubridate)
library(INBOtheme)
rm(list = ls())
wordsforfilter <- c("стратегия", "государственный национальный политика", "национальный политика")
df_mystem_unique <- readRDS("df_mystem_unique.RDS")

df <- readRDS("df0-all-news-2.RDS")
df <- df[!duplicated(df$link),]
df %>% filter(!site=="region.council.gov.ru", postdate > as.POSIXct("2019-01-01", tz="MSK")) -> df

# 1
#####
df %>%
   unnest_tokens(output = term, input = text, token = "words", to_lower = TRUE) ->  ngrams1
ngrams1 %>% filter(term %in% wordsforfilter) -> ngrams1_filtered

# 2
#####
bigrams <- df %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, text, token = "ngrams", n = 2)

bigrams_separated <- bigrams %>%
  separate(bigram, c("word1", "word2"), sep = " ")

bigrams_separated <- left_join(bigrams_separated, df_mystem_unique %>% rename(word1=word, uword1=mystemuniquewords), by = c("word1"))
bigrams_separated <- left_join(bigrams_separated, df_mystem_unique %>% rename(word2=word, uword2=mystemuniquewords), by = c("word2"))

bigrams_separated$term <- str_c(bigrams_separated$uword1,bigrams_separated$uword2, sep = " ", collapse = NULL)
bigrams_separated %>% select(-word1,-word2, -uword1, -uword2) %>% filter(term %in% wordsforfilter) -> bigrams_filtered

# 3
#####
ngrams3 <- df %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, text, token = "ngrams", n = 3)

ngrams3_separated <- ngrams3 %>%
  separate(bigram, c("word1", "word2", "word3"), sep = " ")

ngrams3_separated <- left_join(ngrams3_separated, df_mystem_unique %>% rename(word1=word, uword1=mystemuniquewords), by = c("word1"))
ngrams3_separated <- left_join(ngrams3_separated, df_mystem_unique %>% rename(word2=word, uword2=mystemuniquewords), by = c("word2"))
ngrams3_separated <- left_join(ngrams3_separated, df_mystem_unique %>% rename(word3=word, uword3=mystemuniquewords), by = c("word3"))

ngrams3_separated$term <- str_c(ngrams3_separated$uword1,ngrams3_separated$uword2, ngrams3_separated$uword3, sep = " ", collapse = NULL)

ngrams3_separated %>% select(-word1,-word2, -word3, -uword1, -uword2, -uword3) %>% filter(term %in% wordsforfilter) -> ngrams3_filtered

df_filtered <- rbind(ngrams1_filtered, bigrams_filtered, ngrams3_filtered)
df_filtered %>% 
  mutate(month = factor(month(postdate, label = FALSE, abbr = TRUE))) -> df_filtered

Каждое упоминание term в отдельной строке:

datatable(df_filtered,options = list(pageLength = 5))

Сгруппировано по term, site и посчитано количество. Итог по группировке в отдельной строке:

datatable(df_filtered %>% 
  count(term, site),options = list(pageLength = 5))

Сгруппировано по term, site, month и посчитано количество. Итог по группировке в отдельной строке:

datatable(df_filtered %>% 
  count(term, site, month),options = list(pageLength = 5))
df_filtered %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = month))+geom_bar()+facet_wrap(term~site, scales="free_y") -> g
print(g)

df_filtered %>% ggplot(aes(x = month, fill=site))+geom_bar() -> g
print(g)

df_filtered  %>% group_by(month, site, term) %>% summarise(n=n()) %>% mutate(prop=n/sum(n)) %>% ungroup() %>% ggplot(aes(x = month, y = prop, fill = site)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "fill",stat = "identity")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format())+
  facet_wrap(~term, ncol = 2) -> g
print(g)
